{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "Curated coin dictionary for src/filtering/keyword_filter.py. Each coin lists the full name(s) and safe (unambiguous) ticker(s) that identify it in a market's slug/question. Coins whose common name or ticker collides with an ordinary English word, a person's name, or another well-known non-crypto term (TRUMP, TON, LINK-as-word, OP, MAKER-as-word, ...) are deliberately left out of matching rather than special-cased -- a market about them may simply be missed, which is an accepted trade-off, not a bug.",
    "matching_rules": {
      "names": "matched case-insensitively, on word boundaries, against the market slug and (as a fallback) the question text.",
      "tickers": "matched case-insensitively as a whole token against the slug (slugs are already lowercase, so there's no case signal to check). Against the question text, tickers must appear in ALL CAPS on a word boundary -- this is what stops a ticker like SOL from matching a lowercase/mixed-case word or name in ordinary prose."
    }
  },
